               <head>‘Abd al-Haqq Dihlavi’s Madarij un-nabuvvah</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Madārij al-nabuvvah by ʻAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn Dihlavī, 1551-1642</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2007003439 https://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008121357" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_59x-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_45690112">ʻAbd al-Ḥaqq ibn Sayf al-Dīn Dihlavī, 1551-1642</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_45690112">ابو محمّد عبد الحقّ دهلوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21778">Madārij al-nabuvvah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21778">مدارج النبوّة</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Treatise on Prophetic traditions by the famous muḥaddis̲ of Delhi, Shaykh ʿAbd al-Ḥaqq Dihlavī Bukhārī
</p>
                        <p>Defective at beginning and end
</p>
                        <p>Heavily annotated in parts
</p>
                        <p>Loose slip (foliated as f. 233), the recto side of which is impressed with a seal (obliterated) and owner’s inscription by Niẓām al-Dīn Muḥammad Shāh (or Panāh) ibn Shaykh al-Islām Mawlavī Qivām al-Dīn Muḥammad al-Taqī ibn Shaykh al-Islām Mawlavī Muʿizz al-Dīn Amān Allāh al-shahīd ibn Mawlavī Khayr al-Dīn Abū al-Khayr 1222/1807-8
</p>
                        <p>Covers consisting of outer leather from a later blind-tooled binding without its stiffened paper core, slightly taller in height than the text block (235 x 127)
</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian &amp; Arabic</textLang>
